{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778536460955,"sessionID":"ses_1e711f7abffeZ85Pg1nnIOdGZL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"chatcmpl-tool-8ef8bb35e69640a3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"peripheral nervous system"},"output":"Found 1116 matches (showing first 100)\n/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/__issue_context__.json:\n  Line 2:   \"body\": \"**Uberon term**\\nUBERON:0001629\\ncarotid body\\n\\n**Suggested revision and reasons**\\n\\nThe current parentage of this term indicate that it is part of \\\"common carotid artery plus branches\\\" (UBERON:0001530), which is incorrect. \\n\\nAccording to PMID:[32965908](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32965908), and according to the current definition, \\\"carotid body is a sensory organ in the peripheral nervous system located in the adventitia of the bifurcation of the common carotid artery\\\". \\nWhile the structure is \\\"adjacent to\\\", it is not \\\"part of: the  \\\"common carotid artery plus branches\\\" \\n\\nAccording to the information above, this term should be part of the peripheral nervous system.\",\n\n  Line 25:       \"body\": \"## Issue Fixed ✅\\n\\nI have successfully reclassified the carotid body (UBERON:0001629) to correctly place it within the peripheral nervous system rather than the cardiovascular system.\\n\\n### Changes Made:\\n- **Relationship corrected**: Removed \\n- **New relationship**: Added  \\n- **Evidence added**: Included PMID:32965908 reference to support the classification\\n- **Issue tracking**: Added proper metadata linking to this issue (#3591)\\n\\n### Scientific Rationale:\\nThe carotid body is functionally and developmentally a sensory organ of the peripheral nervous system. While anatomically located adjacent to the carotid artery bifurcation, it is not structurally part of the cardiovascular system. The previous classification was based on location rather than the organ's true biological function and developmental origin.\\n\\n### Next Steps:\\n- **Pull Request**: #3594 is ready for review\\n- **Branch**: \\n- **Validation**: All ontology QA checks have passed\\n\\nThe fix ensures the carotid body is properly classified according to its role as a chemoreceptive sensory organ within the peripheral nervous system, as supported by the referenced literature.\\n\\n**@dragon-ai-agent**\",\n\n\n/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/__pr_result__/uberon-with-isa.obo:\n  Line 2852: name: peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 2942: def: \"Part of peripheral nervous system that includes the somatic parts of the cranial and spinal nerves and their ganglia and the peripheral sensory receptors.\" [NIFSTD:nlx_anat_100301]\n\n  Line 2947: synonym: \"somatic part of peripheral nervous system\" EXACT [UBERON:cjm]\n\n  Line 2948: synonym: \"somatic peripheral nervous system\" EXACT [NIFSTD:nlx_anat_100301]\n\n  Line 2958: relationship: part_of UBERON:0000010 ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 3718: synonym: \"spinal ganglion part of peripheral nervous system\" EXACT [NIFSTD:birnlex_2598]\n\n  Line 4414: def: \"Any part or collection of parts of the central or peripheral nervous system. Parts may span both CNS and PNS.\" [NIFSTD:birnlex_1157]\n\n  Line 5446: relationship: part_of UBERON:0000010 ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 5464: relationship: part_of UBERON:0000010 ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 13354: def: \"An enclosed, cable-like bundle of axons in the peripheral nervous system originating in a nerve root in the central nervous system (or a condensed nervous structure) connecting with peripheral structures.\" [FBbt:00005105, http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165]\n\n  Line 13402: relationship: part_of UBERON:0000010 ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 13550: def: \"The outermost nucleated cytoplasmic layer of Schwann cells that surrounds the axon of the neuron. It forms the outermost layer of the nerve fiber in the peripheral nervous system. The neurolemma is underlain by the basal lamina (referred to as the medullary sheath in the included illustrations. In CNS, axons are myelinated by oligodendrocytes, thus lack neurolemma.\" [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neurolemma]\n\n  Line 13567: relationship: part_of UBERON:0000010 ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 31946: synonym: \"cranial ganglion part of peripheral nervous system\" EXACT [NIFSTD:birnlex_2597]\n\n  Line 34591: def: \"The clusters of neurons in the somatic peripheral nervous system which contain the cell bodies of sensory nerve axons, interneurons and non-neuronal supporting cells.\" [MP:0000960]\n\n  Line 34752: is_a: UBERON:0003338  ! ganglion of peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 34875: def: \"Anatomical junction where subdivisions of two or more neural trees interconnect with one another to form a network through which nerve fibers of the constituent nerve trees become regrouped; together with other nerve plexuses, nerves and ganglia, it constitutes the peripheral nervous system. Examples: cervical nerve plexus, brachial nerve plexus, sacral nerve plexus[FMA].\" [FMA:5901, http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nervous_system_plexus]\n\n  Line 41002: def: \"A cable-like bundle of peripheral axons (the long, slender projections of neurons). A nerve provides a common pathway for the electrochemical nerve impulses that are transmitted along each of the axons. Nerves are found only in the peripheral nervous system. In the central nervous system, the analogous structures are known as tracts[WP].\" [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peripheral_nerve]\n\n  Line 41008: synonym: \"nerve part of peripheral nervous system\" EXACT [NIFSTD:birnlex_1615]\n\n  Line 52944: synonym: \"autonomic division of peripheral nervous system\" EXACT [FMA:65553]\n\n  Line 52945: synonym: \"autonomic part of peripheral nervous system\" EXACT [FMA:65553]\n\n  Line 52975: relationship: part_of UBERON:0000010 ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 63491: is_a: UBERON:0003338  ! ganglion of peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 69477: relationship: part_of UBERON:0000010 ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 69939: def: \"neural crest cells (NCCs) originating in the anterior part of the developing embryo and residing between the mid-diencephalon and the forming hindbrain; cranial NCCs migrate dorsolaterally to form the craniofacial mesenchyme that differentiates into various craniofacial cartilages and bones, cranial neurons, glia, and connective tissues of the face; these cells enter the pharyngeal pouches and arches where they give rise to thymic cells, bones of the middle ear and jaw (mandible), and the odontoblasts of the tooth primordia; like their counterparts in the trunk, cranial NCCs also contribute to the developing peripheral nervous system, along with the pigmented cell (i.e. melanocyte) lineage.\" [MGI:anna]\n\n  Line 73848: name: ganglion of peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 73852: synonym: \"peripheral nervous system ganglion\" EXACT [OBOL:automatic]\n\n  Line 73858: relationship: part_of UBERON:0000010 ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 73860: intersection_of: part_of UBERON:0000010 ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 108324: synonym: \"autonomic division of peripheral nervous system\" EXACT [FMA:65553]\n\n  Line 108325: synonym: \"autonomic part of peripheral nervous system\" EXACT [FMA:65553]\n\n  Line 116765: def: \"A threadlike extension of a nerve cell and consists of an axon and myelin sheath (if it is myelinated) in the nervous system. There are nerve fibers in the central nervous system and peripheral nervous system. A nerve fiber may be myelinated and/or unmyelinated. In the central nervous system (CNS), myelin by oligodendroglia cells is formed. Schwann cells form myelin in the peripheral nervous system (PNS). Schwann cells also make a thin covering in an axon without myelin (in the PNS). A peripheral nerve fiber contains an axon, myelin sheath, schwann cells and its endoneurium. There are no endoneurium and schwann cells in the central nervous system.\" [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nervous_system_fiber]\n\n  Line 125835: relationship: part_of UBERON:0000010 ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 141654: relationship: in_lateral_side_of UBERON:0000010 ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 191498: name: obsolete regional part of peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 191502: synonym: \"regional part of peripheral nervous system\" EXACT HUMAN_PREFERRED [NIFSTD:birnlex_1122]\n\n  Line 193220: name: ganglion part of peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 193223: synonym: \"ganglion part of peripheral nervous system\" EXACT HUMAN_PREFERRED [NIFSTD:birnlex_2548]\n\n  Line 193226: relationship: part_of UBERON:0000010 ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 237587: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 244083: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 247269: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 250108: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 250224: is_a: UBERON:0003338  ! ganglion of peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 255514: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 262641: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 267634: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 271236: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 275631: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 283741: is_a: UBERON:0003338  ! ganglion of peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 293256: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 294766: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 318525: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 321284: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 326611: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 330237: is_a: UBERON:0003338  ! ganglion of peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 338782: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 344572: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 345726: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 347220: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 363829: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 372486: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 378405: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 381228: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 386407: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 388814: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 397032: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 399260: is_a: UBERON:0003338  ! ganglion of peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 399261: is_a: UBERON:0024940  ! ganglion part of peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 405370: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 411749: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 417872: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 424408: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 438904: is_a: UBERON:0000010  ! peripheral nervous system\n\n\n/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/__pr_result__/uberon-taxmod-amniote.obo:\n  Line 488: name: peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 534: property_value: external_definition \"The peripheral nervous system (PNS) is the part of the nervous system connected to the CNS which contains cranial nerves III - XII, spinal, peripheral and autonomic nerves. (CUMBO)\" xsd:string {source=\"Cumbo:terms\"}\n\n  Line 586: def: \"Part of peripheral nervous system that includes the somatic parts of the cranial and spinal nerves and their ganglia and the peripheral sensory receptors.\" [NLXANAT:100301]\n\n  Line 591: synonym: \"somatic part of peripheral nervous system\" EXACT [UBERON:cjm]\n\n  Line 592: synonym: \"somatic peripheral nervous system\" EXACT [NLXANAT:100301]\n\n  Line 602: relationship: part_of UBERON:0000010 ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 1366: synonym: \"spinal ganglion part of peripheral nervous system\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:2598]\n\n  Line 1979: def: \"Any part or collection of parts of the central or peripheral nervous system. Parts may span both CNS and PNS.\" [BIRNLEX:1157]\n\n  Line 3061: relationship: part_of UBERON:0000010 ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 3079: relationship: part_of UBERON:0000010 ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 10844: property_value: external_definition \"A regulatory system of the body that consists of neurons and neuroglial cells. The nervous system is divided into two parts, the central nervous system (CNS) and the peripheral nervous system (PNS). (Source: BioGlossary, www.Biology-Text.com)[TAO]\" xsd:string {date_retrieved=\"2012-08-14\", external_class=\"TAO:0000396\", ontology=\"TAO\", source=\"ZFIN:curator\"}\n\n  Line 10980: def: \"An enclosed, cable-like bundle of axons in the peripheral nervous system originating in a nerve root in the central nervous system (or a condensed nervous structure) connecting with peripheral structures.\" [FBbt:00005105, http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165]\n\n  Line 11028: relationship: part_of UBERON:0000010 ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 11172: def: \"The outermost nucleated cytoplasmic layer of Schwann cells that surrounds the axon of the neuron. It forms the outermost layer of the nerve fiber in the peripheral nervous system. The neurolemma is underlain by the basal lamina (referred to as the medullary sheath in the included illustrations. In CNS, axons are myelinated by oligodendrocytes, thus lack neurolemma.\" [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neurolemma]\n\n  Line 11188: relationship: part_of UBERON:0000010 ! peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 30200: synonym: \"cranial ganglion part of peripheral nervous system\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:2597]\n\n  Line 32991: def: \"The clusters of neurons in the somatic peripheral nervous system which contain the cell bodies of sensory nerve axons, interneurons and non-neuronal supporting cells.\" [MP:0000960]\n\n  Line 33155: is_a: UBERON:0003338 ! ganglion of peripheral nervous system\n\n  Line 33279: def: \"Anatomical junction where subdivisions of two or more neural trees interconnect with one another to form a network through which nerve fibers of the constituent nerve trees become regrouped; together with other nerve plexuses, nerves and ganglia, it constitutes the peripheral nervous system. Examples: cervical nerve plexus, brachial nerve plexus, sacral nerve plexus[FMA].\" [FMA:5901, http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nervous_system_plexus]\n\n  Line 39730: def: \"A cable-like bundle of peripheral axons (the long, slender projections of neurons). A nerve provides a common pathway for the electrochemical nerve impulses that are transmitted along each of the axons. Nerves are found only in the peripheral nervous system. In the central nervous system, the analogous structures are known as tracts[WP].\" [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peripheral_nerve]\n\n  Line 39734: synonym: \"nerve part of peripheral nervous system\" EXACT [BIRNLEX:1615]\n\n  Line 52257: synonym: \"autonomic division of peripheral nervous system\" EXACT [FMA:65553]\n\n  Line 52258: synonym: \"autonomic part of peripheral nervous system\" EXACT [FMA:65553]\n\n  Line 52290: relationship: part_of UBERON:0000010 {source=\"EMAPA\", source=\"MA\", source=\"NIFSTD\", source=\"ZFA-modified-from-isa\"} ! peripheral nervous system\n\n\n(Results truncated: showing 100 of 1116 matches (1016 hidden). Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":1116,"truncated":true},"title":"peripheral nervous system","time":{"start":1778536460835,"end":1778536460953}},"id":"prt_e1908b11e001NQyvoJii2LfoYM","sessionID":"ses_1e711f7abffeZ85Pg1nnIOdGZL","messageID":"msg_e19083cd0001Wuya0EfDb9rU8t"}}
